.SH "NAME"
scsi_get_device_flags \- get device specific flags from the dynamic device list\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ scsi_get_device_flags('u
.BI "int scsi_get_device_flags(struct\ scsi_device\ *\ " "sdev" ", const\ unsigned\ char\ *\ " "vendor" ", const\ unsigned\ char\ *\ " "model" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIsdev\fR
.RS 4
scsi_device
to get flags for
.RE
.PP
\fIvendor\fR
.RS 4
vendor name
.RE
.PP
\fImodel\fR
.RS 4
model name
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Search the global scsi_dev_info_list (specified by list zero) for an entry matching
\fIvendor\fR
and
\fImodel\fR, if found, return the matching flags value, else return the host or global default settings\&. Called during scan time\&.
